'''Merih Demiral''' (born 5 March 1998) is a Turkish professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[Saudi Pro League]] club [[Al Ahli Saudi FC|Al-Ahli]] and [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]].

==Club career==
===Early years===
Product of the [[Fenerbahçe S.K.|Fenerbahçe]] youth system, Demiral was signed by Portuguese side [[A.C. Alcanenense|Alcanenense]] in 2016.<ref name="ojogo1">{{cite web |url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/sporting/noticias/turco-merih-demiral-chega-emprestado-5598761.html |title=Turco Merih Demiral chega emprestado |trans-title=Turk Merih Demiral is loaned out |last1=Toucedo |first1=Rafael |work=O Jogo |language=pt |date=11 January 2017 |access-date=15 January 2020 |archive-date=15 January 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200115161446/https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/sporting/noticias/turco-merih-demiral-chega-emprestado-5598761.html |url-status=live }}</ref> On 16 October 2016, he made his [[Taça de Portugal]] debut against [[CD Feirense|Feirense]] in a 2-1 home loss.{{citation needed|date=September 2025}}

===Sporting===
In January 2017, he was loaned out to [[Sporting Clube de Portugal B|Sporting B]], and made his professional debut in the [[Segunda Liga]] for the latter club on 5 February 2017 in a 1–1 home draw against [[F.C. Famalicão|Famalicão]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2017/02/05/portugal/liga-de-honra/sporting-b/fc-famalicao/2284530/|title=Game Report by Soccerway|publisher=Soccerway|date=5 February 2017|access-date=21 February 2018|archive-date=11 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180711053759/https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2017/02/05/portugal/liga-de-honra/sporting-b/fc-famalicao/2284530/|url-status=live}}</ref> At the end of the season, he was signed outright by the club.<ref name="ojogo2">{{cite web |url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/sporting/noticias/demiral-quer-convencer-jesus-na-pre-temporada-8518737.html |title=Demiral quer convencer Jesus na pré-temporada |trans-title=Demiral wants to convince Jesus during the pre-season |last=Tornesi |first=Duarte |work=O Jogo |language=pt |date=30 May 2017 |access-date=15 January 2020 |archive-date=15 January 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200115161442/https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/sporting/noticias/demiral-quer-convencer-jesus-na-pre-temporada-8518737.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 12 July 2017, he made his first and only performance with [[Sporting Clube de Portugal|Sporting]] in a 2-4 [[2017–18 Taça de Portugal#Third round|Taça de Portugal]] third round away win against [[ARC Oleiros|Oleiros]] as a late substitute.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/taca-portugal/12-10-2017/tp-arc-oleiros-sporting-2-4-resultado-final |title=TP: ARC Oleiros-Sporting, 2-4 (resultado final) |work=maisfutebol.pt |date=12 July 2017 |access-date=16 September 2025 |language=pt}}</ref>{{citation needed|date=September 2025}}

====Loan to Alanyaspor====
On 15 August 2018, he joined Turkish club [[Alanyaspor]] on loan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.alanyaspor.org.tr/Haberler-ID-763-haberler-transfer-hosgeldin-merih-demiral|title=Hoşgeldin Merih Demiral!|trans-title=Welcome to Merih Demiral!|publisher=[[Alanyaspor]]|language=tr|date=15 August 2018|access-date=26 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181224032605/http://www.alanyaspor.org.tr/Haberler-ID-763-Haberler-transfer-hosgeldin-merih-demiral|archive-date=24 December 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 29 January 2019, he permanently joined Alanyaspor for €3.5 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gazetefutbol.de/deadline-day-gazetefutbols-transferticker/|title=Deadline-Day: GazeteFutbols Transferticker|first=Anil P. Polat Stellvertretender Chefredakteur GazeteFutbol|publisher=gazetefutbol.de|language=de|last=Hürriyet.de-Redaktion|date=31 January 2019|access-date=28 March 2019|archive-date=28 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190328043025/https://gazetefutbol.de/deadline-day-gazetefutbols-transferticker/|url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Sassuolo ===
On 30 January 2019, Demiral joined Italian club [[U.S. Sassuolo Calcio|Sassuolo]] on loan with an obligation to buy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.tuttomercatoweb.com/serie-a/ufficiale-sassuolo-arriva-demiral-in-prestito-con-obbligo-di-riscatto-1208471|title=UFFICIALE: Sassuolo, arriva Demiral in prestito con obbligo di riscatto|trans-title=OFFICIAL: Sassuolo, Demiral arrives on loan with an obbligation to buy|publisher=tuttomercatoweb.com|language=it|access-date=30 January 2019|archive-date=9 June 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190609082956/https://m.tuttomercatoweb.com/serie-a/ufficiale-sassuolo-arriva-demiral-in-prestito-con-obbligo-di-riscatto-1208471|url-status=live}}</ref> He made his [[Serie A]] and club debut on 24 February, in a 1–1 home draw against [[S.P.A.L.|SPAL]],<ref name="Pergolizzi">{{cite web|last=Pergolizzi|first=Dario|date=29 May 2019|title=Perché la Juventus vuole prendere Demiral|trans-title=Why Juventus want to get Demiral|url=https://www.ultimouomo.com/demiral-juventus-sassuolo/|publisher=www.ultimouomo.com|language=it|access-date=14 January 2020|archive-date=29 June 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190629115431/https://www.ultimouomo.com/demiral-juventus-sassuolo/|url-status=live}}</ref> and scored his first goals both for the club and in Serie A—a brace in a 4–0 home win over [[A.C. ChievoVerona|Chievo]]—on 4 April.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.calcionews24.com/sassuolo-primo-gol-demiral-serie-a/ |title=Sassuolo, doppietta da sogno per Demiral: prime gioie in Serie A! |trans-title=Sassuolo, dream-like brace for Demiral: first joys in Serie A! |publisher=www.calcionews24.com |language=it |date=4 April 2019 |access-date=15 January 2020 |archive-date=15 January 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200115162042/https://www.calcionews24.com/sassuolo-primo-gol-demiral-serie-a/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Juventus===
On 5 July 2019, [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] officially announced the transfer of Demiral from Sassuolo, on a five-year contract for €18 million.<ref name="Demiral to Juventus">{{cite news|title=Official: Merih Demiral is Bianconero!|url=https://www.juventus.com/en/news/news/2019/merih-demiral---bianconero-.php|publisher=[[Juventus FC]]|date=5 July 2019|access-date=5 July 2019|archive-url=https://archive.today/20190705191518/https://www.juventus.com/en/news/news/2019/merih-demiral---bianconero-.php|archive-date=5 July 2019|quote="The Turkish defender joins Juventus from Sassuolo: he will be a Bianconeri until 30 June 2024."|url-status=live}}</ref> His salary was reportedly unfolded as [[Euro|€]]1.3 million per year.<ref name="Juventus Salary">{{cite news|title=Merih Demiral'ın Juventus'taki maaşı belli oldu|url=https://skor.sozcu.com.tr/2019/07/14/merih-demiralin-juventustaki-maasi-belli-oldu-1352626/|publisher=[[Sözcü]]|access-date=14 July 2019|language=Tr|archive-url=https://archive.today/20190714111531/https://skor.sozcu.com.tr/2019/07/14/merih-demiralin-juventustaki-maasi-belli-oldu-1352626/|archive-date=14 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> He became the first Turkish player to play for the club.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.calciomercato.com/en/news/demiral-being-the-first-juve-turk-is-an-honor-chiellini-helps-me-77528 |title=Demiral: 'Being the first Juve turk is an honor, Chiellini helps me a lot' |publisher=www.calciomercato.com |date=20 August 2019 |access-date=17 January 2020 |archive-date=29 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229194748/https://www.calciomercato.com/en/news/demiral-being-the-first-juve-turk-is-an-honor-chiellini-helps-me-77528 |url-status=live }}</ref> He made his club debut on 21 September, in a 2–1 home win over [[Hellas Verona F.C.|Verona]] in Serie A.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.tuttosport.com/news/calcio/serie-a/2019/09/21-61420528/serie_a_juve-verona_2-1_ramsey_e_cristiano_ronaldo_firmano_la_rimonta/ |title=Serie A, Juve-Verona 2-1: Ramsey e Cristiano Ronaldo firmano la rimonta |trans-title=Serie A, Juve–Verona 2–1: Ramsey and Cristiano Ronaldo mark the comeback |work=Tutto Sport |language=it |last1=Vaciago |first1=Guido |date=21 September 2019 |access-date=22 September 2019 |archive-date=22 September 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190922132003/https://www.tuttosport.com/news/calcio/serie-a/2019/09/21-61420528/serie_a_juve-verona_2-1_ramsey_e_cristiano_ronaldo_firmano_la_rimonta/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He subsequently made his [[2019–20 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] debut on 11 December, in the club's final group match, earning praise in the media for his performance as he helped Juventus keep a clean sheet in a 2–0 away win over [[Bayer Leverkusen]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2027111--leverkusen-vs-juventus/ |title=Leverkusen 0–2 Juventus |publisher=[[UEFA]] |last1=Thorogood |first1=James |date=11 December 2019 |access-date=13 January 2020 |archive-date=27 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191227051507/https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/season=2020/matches/round=2001140/match=2027111/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/it/notizie/juventus-demiral-da-urlo-contro-bayer-leverkusen/lxhbpk6jqoa41qvuukb9st5wi |title=Juventus, Demiral da urlo contro il Bayer Leverkusen: arma in più per Sarri |trans-title=Juventus, Demiral outstanding against Bayer Leverkusen: an additional asset for Sarri |publisher=Goal.com |language=it |last1=Agresti |first1=Romeo |date=13 December 2019 |access-date=13 January 2020 |archive-date=13 January 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200113173039/https://www.goal.com/it/notizie/juventus-demiral-da-urlo-contro-bayer-leverkusen/lxhbpk6jqoa41qvuukb9st5wi |url-status=live }}</ref>

He scored his first goal for the club on 12 January 2020, the opener in a 2–1 away win over [[A.S. Roma|Roma]], which saw Juventus secure the unofficial title of "Winter Champions", though he was later substituted for [[Matthijs de Ligt]] after sustaining an [[anterior cruciate ligament]] injury. As a result, he was expected to be ruled out for the remainder of the season, including [[UEFA Euro 2020|Euro 2020]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/jan/12/roma-juventus-psg-monaco-hellas-verona-genoa |title=Euro roundup: Zaniolo and Demiral likely to miss Euros after rupturing ACLs |work=The Guardian |date=13 January 2020 |access-date=13 January 2020 |archive-date=8 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200308103646/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/jan/12/roma-juventus-psg-monaco-hellas-verona-genoa |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.football-italia.net/SerieA/match/142546 |title=Roma 1 - 2 Juventus |publisher=Football Italia |date=12 January 2020 |access-date=13 January 2020 |archive-date=16 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316061248/https://www.football-italia.net/SerieA/match/142546 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Juventus/12-01-2020/quarto-d-ora-gol-infortunio-demiral-gioia-tanta-dolore-forte-36045562818.shtml |title=Demiral dalla gioia (del gol) al dolore (dell'infortunio): distorsione al ginocchio, domattina il verdetto |trans-title=Demiral from joy (for his goal) to pain (for his injury): knee strain, tomorrow the verdict |work=La Gazzetta dello Sport |language=it |date=12 January 2020 |access-date=13 January 2020 |archive-date=13 January 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200113125831/https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Juventus/12-01-2020/quarto-d-ora-gol-infortunio-demiral-gioia-tanta-dolore-forte-36045562818.shtml |url-status=live }}</ref> He returned to action on 1 August, featuring as a substitute in Juventus' 3–1 home defeat to Roma in Serie A, with Juventus already confirmed as league champions.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.tuttosport.com/news/calcio/serie-a/2020/08/01-72394010/juve-roma_1-3_higuain_non_basta_ora_testa_alla_champions/ |title=Juve-Roma 1-3: Higuain non basta, ora testa alla Champions |work=www.tuttosport.com |language=it |last1=Baldini |first1=Sergio |date=1 August 2020 |access-date=2 August 2020 |archive-date=3 August 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200803092332/https://www.tuttosport.com/news/calcio/serie-a/2020/08/01-72394010/juve-roma_1-3_higuain_non_basta_ora_testa_alla_champions/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

==== Loan to Atalanta ====
On 6 August 2021, [[Atalanta B.C.|Atalanta]] announced the signing of Demiral from [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] on loan with an option to buy.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Benvenuto Demiral!|url=https://www.atalanta.it/news/benvenuto-demiral/|date=6 August 2021|website=atalanta.it|language=it|access-date=6 August 2021|archive-date=6 August 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210806145423/https://www.atalanta.it/news/benvenuto-demiral/|url-status=live}}</ref> During the [[2021–22 Atalanta B.C. season|2021–22 season]], he accumulated a total of 42 appearances in all competitions, scored two goals, and provided three assists. Atalanta exercised the right to buy on 17 June 2022 for a fee of €20 million.<ref name=ata-def>{{cite web |url=https://www.atalanta.it/ |title=Demiral: esercitato il diritto di opzione |website=atalanta.it |language=it |date=17 June 2022 |access-date=6 August 2021 |archive-date=4 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210804125915/https://www.atalanta.it/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=FI622>{{cite web |url=https://football-italia.net/atalanta-to-purchase-demiral-from-juventus-after-all/ |title=Atalanta to purchase Demiral from Juventus after all |last=Campanale |first=Susy |publisher=Football Italia |date=17 June 2022 |access-date=17 June 2022 |archive-date=17 June 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220617184031/https://football-italia.net/atalanta-to-purchase-demiral-from-juventus-after-all/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

=== Al-Ahli ===
On 19 August 2023, Demiral joined [[Saudi Pro League]] club [[Al Ahli Saudi FC|Al-Ahli]] on a three-year contract for a reported fee of €17 million.<ref>{{cite web |title=الأهلي يواصل صفقاته القوية ويضم "المقاتل" دميرال |work=جريدة الرياض |url=https://www.alriyadh.com/2028248 |access-date=19 August 2023 |archive-date=19 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230819154439/http://www.alriyadh.com/2028248 |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 24 August 2023, he made his debut with the team against [[Al-Okhdood Club|Al-Okhdood]] in a 1-0 [[Saudi Pro League]] win. On 22 December 2023, he scored his first goal with the team and also made his first assist against [[Al-Fayha FC|Al-Fayha]] in a 0-4 [[Saudi Pro League]] away match win.

On 16 September 2024, he made his [[AFC Champions League Elite]] debut against [[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]] in a 1-0 home win. He played all [[2024–25 AFC Champions League Elite]] matches and helped the team to win the trophy with his performance.

==International career==
[[File:Demiral in the international match in September 2020 (Cropped).jpg|thumb|175px|Demiral with [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]] in 2020]]
Demiral represented Turkey at junior levels, including [[Turkey national under-17 football team|Under-17]] and [[Turkey national under-19 football team|Under-19]]. He made his debut for the [[Turkey national football team|senior squad]] on 20 November 2018 in a friendly against [[Ukraine national football team|Ukraine]], as an 85th-minute substitute for [[Mert Müldür]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[ESPN]]|url=http://www.espn.co.uk/soccer/match?gameId=520333|title=Turkey v Ukraine game report|date=20 November 2018|access-date=26 November 2018|archive-date=26 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181126221427/http://www.espn.co.uk/soccer/match?gameId=520333|url-status=live}}</ref> On 11 June 2021, Demiral scored an [[own goal]] in a 3–0 defeat against [[Italy national football team|Italy]] in the first game of the [[UEFA Euro 2020]] campaign; it was the first time in the tournament's history that the match opener kicked off with an own goal.<ref>{{Cite web|title='Juve's in his blood!' – Turkish defender Demiral nets historic own goal to open Euro 2020 against Italy {{!}} Goal.com|url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/juves-in-his-blood-turkish-defender-demiral-nets-historic/nw6ifg89t4dczbg0y2hochaa|access-date=2021-06-11|website=goal.com|archive-date=9 August 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210809102053/https://www.goal.com/en/news/juves-in-his-blood-turkish-defender-demiral-nets-historic/nw6ifg89t4dczbg0y2hochaa|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 7 June 2024, he was selected in the 26-man squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |date=7 June 2024 |title=A Millî Takımımızın EURO 2024 Aday Kadrosu Açıklandı |trans-title=EURO 2024 Candidate Squad of Our National Team Announced |url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=44561 |language=tr |publisher=Turkish Football Federation |access-date=7 June 2024 |archive-date=7 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240607205837/https://tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=44561 |url-status=live }}</ref> In the round of 16 match against [[Austria national football team|Austria]], he was awarded player of the match by scoring a brace in a 2–1 victory, securing his country's qualification to the quarter-finals.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/match/2036204--austria-vs-turkiye/ |title=Austria 1–2 Türkiye |publisher=UEFA |date=2 July 2024 |access-date=2 July 2024 |archive-date=2 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240702212650/https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/match/2036204--austria-vs-turkiye/ |url-status=live }}</ref> His first goal, netted just 57 seconds into the game, set a record as the fastest goal in the knockout stages of the European competition.<ref>{{cite web |last=Fitzpatrick |first=Peter |url=https://onefootball.com/fr/news/demiral-makes-euros-knockout-history-with-rapid-quick-goal-vs-austria-39708672 |title=Demiral makes EUROs knockout history with rapid-quick goal vs Austria 😲 |publisher=OneFootball |date=2 July 2024 |access-date=2 July 2024 |archive-date=3 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240703164106/https://onefootball.com/fr/news/demiral-makes-euros-knockout-history-with-rapid-quick-goal-vs-austria-39708672 |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 14 October 2025, he scored twice in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group E|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]] match against [[Georgia national football team|Georgia]] in [[Kocaeli Stadium]], in [[İzmit|Kocaeli]] where he was born.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2025/10/turkiye-4-1-gurcistan |title=Türkiye 4-1 Gürcistan
 |publisher=Fenerbahce.org |date=15 October 2025 |access-date=15 October 2025 |language=tr }}</ref>

===Military salute during the Euro 2020 qualifier===
On 11 October 2019, following [[Cenk Tosun]]'s goal in a 1–0 home win over [[Albania national football team|Albania]] in a [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying|Euro 2020 qualifier]], Demiral was one of the Turkish players who participated in a controversial "[[Salute#Military salutes|military salute]]" [[goal celebration]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50019304 |title=Turkey v Albania (1–0) |website=BBC Sport |date=11 October 2019 |access-date=29 October 2019 |archive-date=19 October 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191019102214/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50019304 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.calciomercato.com/en/news/uefa-to-examine-turkey-military-celebrations-calhanoglu-and-demi-82485 |title=UEFA to examine Turkey 'military' celebrations: Calhanoglu and Demiral at risk |website=Calciomercato.com |date=12 October 2019 |access-date=29 October 2019 |archive-date=17 October 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191017125328/https://www.calciomercato.com/en/news/uefa-to-examine-turkey-military-celebrations-calhanoglu-and-demi-82485 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-50041529 |title=Euro 2020: Uefa probes Turkey footballers' military salute |website=BBC Sport |date=14 October 2019 |access-date=29 October 2019 |archive-date=2 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202172312/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-50041529 |url-status=live }}</ref> The same day, he stated his open support for the [[2019 Turkish offensive into north-eastern Syria|Turkish offensive into north-eastern Syria]] on [[Twitter]]; while his post was praised by Turkish supporters, it also drew criticism from numerous football fans of Juventus on social media, as well as those of other clubs, some of whom asked for the club to take disciplinary actions against the player; others even demanded that Demiral be dismissed by the club.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/it/notizie/francia-turchia-demiral-esulta-saluto-militare/1w6f0y9apderw1e5cykuehk98f|title=Francia-Turchia, Demiral protagonista: grande prova e nuovo saluto militare|trans-title=France–Turkey, Demiral protagonist: great performance and new military salute|website=Goal.com|language=it|access-date=15 October 2019|archive-date=22 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191022050654/https://www.goal.com/it/notizie/francia-turchia-demiral-esulta-saluto-militare/1w6f0y9apderw1e5cykuehk98f|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.open.online/2019/10/14/francia-turchia-demiral-ci-ricasca-e-ripropone-il-saluto-militare/|title=Francia-Turchia, lo juventino Demiral insiste: esulta col saluto militare pro-Erdogan|trans-title=France–Turkey, the Juventus player Demiral insists: celebrates with a pro–Erdogan military salute|website=Open|language=it|date=14 October 2019|access-date=15 October 2019|archive-date=24 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191224022406/https://www.open.online/2019/10/14/francia-turchia-demiral-ci-ricasca-e-ripropone-il-saluto-militare/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.calciomercato.com/en/news/demiralout-trending-juventus-fans-want-defender-due-to-political-81989|title=DemiralOut trending: Juventus fans want defender due to political views|website=Calciomercato.com|access-date=17 October 2019|archive-date=22 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191022053305/https://www.calciomercato.com/en/news/demiralout-trending-juventus-fans-want-defender-due-to-political-81989|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://it.eurosport.com/calcio/serie-a/2019-2020/demiral-e-under-nella-bufera-per-i-tweet-a-sostegno-dell-offensiva-in-siria_sto7494708/story.shtml |title=Demiral, Calhanoglu e Under nella bufera per i tweet a sostegno dell'offensiva turca contro i curdi |trans-title=Demiral, Calhanoglu and Under in turbulence for their tweets supporting the Turkish offensive against the Kurds |website=Eurosport |language=it |last=Dolci |first=Stefano |date=11 October 2019 |access-date=29 October 2019 }}</ref>

===Euro 2024 ban and wolf salute===
On 2 July 2024, after the match against [[Austria national football team|Austria]] in the [[UEFA Euro 2024 knockout stage#Round of 16|Euro 2024]] in Germany, Demiral displayed the so-called [[wolf salute]], which is associated with Turkish [[Turkish nationalism|nationalism]], [[pan-Turkism]], and the [[Grey Wolves (organization)|Grey Wolves organization]].<ref name="автоссылка1">{{cite book |author=Matusitz, Jonathan |chapter= |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SS-PBAAAQBAJ |title=Symbolism in Terrorism: Motivation, Communication, and Behavior |location= |date=2014 |publisher=[[Rowman & Littlefield|Rowman & Littlefield Publishers]] |volume= |pages=12 |series= |isbn=9781442235793}}</ref> The salute is banned in Austria.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-07-04 |title=Germany summons Turkish ambassador over rightist 'wolf' goal celebration at soccer tournament |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/germany-euros-soccer-turkey-wolf-goal-celebration-recep-tayyip-erdogan-rcna160315 |access-date=2024-07-05 |website=NBC News |language=en |archive-date=5 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240705074532/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/germany-euros-soccer-turkey-wolf-goal-celebration-recep-tayyip-erdogan-rcna160315 |url-status=live }}</ref> At the press conference, he stated that it was an expression of Turkish pride and he intends to do it again when the opportunity arises. In addition to criticism from politicians and journalists,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/fussball-em-tuerkei-oesterreich-wolfsgruss-demiral-rechtsextrem-uefa-lux.UaK4WonSA6bg5RKE5JWVTw |title=Uefa ermittelt gegen Demiral wegen des 'Wolfsgrußes' |trans-title=Uefa investigation against Demiral because of "Wolf salute" |website=[[Süddeutsche Zeitung]]|language=de |date=3 July 2024 |access-date=3 July 2024|publisher=Südwestdeutsche Medien Holding}}</ref> [[UEFA]] started an investigation for alleged inappropriate behaviour.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.uefa.com/running-competitions/disciplinary/updates/028f-1b472db4c7d7-cdf7c16b8ac8-1000/ |title=UEFA Ethics and Disciplinary Inspector appointed |website=[[UEFA]]|date=3 July 2024 |access-date=3 July 2024}}</ref> On 3 and 4 July 2024 Turkey and Germany respectively summoned the other nations [[ambassador]] to discuss the incident.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.tagesspiegel.de/sport/wegen-demirals-wolfsgruss-berlin-bestellt-turkischen-botschafter-ein-11958566.html |title=Wegen Demirals "Wolfsgruß": Bundesregierung bestellt türkischen Botschafter ein |website=[[Tagesspiegel]] |date=4 July 2024 |access-date=4 July 2024 |archive-date=4 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240704105250/https://www.tagesspiegel.de/sport/wegen-demirals-wolfsgruss-berlin-bestellt-turkischen-botschafter-ein-11958566.html |url-status=live }}</ref> UEFA announced on 5 July that he would be banned for a total of two matches for failing to comply with the general principles of conduct and for violating the basic rules of decent conduct.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.uefa.com/running-competitions/disciplinary/updates/028f-1b4b5df93e8d-2aae45b09ee5-1000/ |title=Appeals Body decision: 2024 European Championship match, Austria - Türkiye |website=[[UEFA]]|date=5 July 2024 |access-date=5 July 2024}}</ref> The [[Turkish Football Federation]] (TFF) said they would appeal the decision to the [[Court of Arbitration for Sport]] (CAS).<ref>{{Cite web |title=Turkey appeals Demiral match ban for extremism; They can still beat Oranje, says Kökçü {{!}} NL Times |url=https://nltimes.nl/2024/07/05/turkey-appeals-demiral-match-ban-extremism-can-still-beat-oranje-says-kokcu |access-date=2024-07-05 |website=nltimes.nl |date=5 July 2024 |language=en}}</ref> TFF president Mehmet Büyükeksi later that day acknowledged that, according to article 63 of UEFA statutes, the CAS has no authority over cases were a player has been banned for less than three matches and there is no way for the TFF to appeal his ban.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.tagesspiegel.de/sport/voreingenommenes-verhalten-gegenuber-auslandern-kein-einspruch-gegen-demiral-sperre-moglich-11968103.html |title= "Voreingenommenes Verhalten gegenüber Ausländern": Kein Einspruch gegen Demiral-Sperre möglich |website=[[Tagesspiegel]]|date=5 July 2024 |access-date=5 July 2024}}</ref> UEFA's ban on Demiral was criticised by some as hypocritical and of double standard by drawing comparisons with the lighter penalty received by [[Jude Bellingham]] for offensive gesture made at the same tournament and with political gestures made by footballers of other nations which had gone unpunished in previous editions of the tournament.<ref>{{cite news |title=Giving Turkish defender Merih Demiral 2-match ban shows UEFA's double standards |url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/sports/giving-turkish-defender-merih-demiral-2-match-ban-shows-uefas-double-standards/3267448 |website=aa.com |access-date=23 July 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=UEFA's 2-match ban on Merih Demiral sparks allegations of Western hypocrisy |url=https://www.turkiyetoday.com/turkiye/uefas-2-match-ban-on-merih-demiral-sparks-allegations-of-western-hypocrisy-26686/ |website=turkiyetoday.com |access-date=23 July 2024}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Demiral is usually deployed as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]], in either a three or four-man defence, although he is a versatile player, who is also capable of playing as a right-sided [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|full-back]].<ref name=":0">{{cite web|date=20 August 2019|title=Demiral looking to learn from 'idol' Chiellini at Juventus|url=https://en.as.com/en/2019/08/20/football/1566337303_759953.html|access-date=17 January 2020|publisher=as.com|archive-date=30 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201130125011/https://en.as.com/en/2019/08/20/football/1566337303_759953.html|url-status=dead}}</ref>

An aggressive and instinctive defender, his main traits are his physicality, tactical intelligence, [[Tackle (association football)|tackling]], composure, and determination, which allow to excel at reading plays, and also enable him to anticipate or [[Marking (association football)|mark]] his opponents well.<ref name=":0" /> A tall and physically strong defender, he is also known for his ability in the air, which enables him to defend opposing [[Cross (association football)|crosses]] and clear the ball away from his own [[penalty area]].<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1">{{cite web|last1=Barbagallo|first1=Anthony|date=29 July 2019|title=Demiral as decisive as De Ligt|url=https://www.football-italia.net/141375/demiral-decisive-de-ligt|access-date=2 August 2020|publisher=Football Italia}}</ref> Despite his tall stature and imposing physique, he is also a mobile defender, which allows him to make recoveries, win back the ball effectively, or restrict his opponents' movements when defending off the ball.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" />

Regarded as a promising young defender in the media, due to his characteristics, he has been compared to [[Nemanja Vidić]], whom Demiral himself has also cited as an inspiration.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.calciomercato.com/news/chi-e-merih-demiral-il-nuovo-vidic-che-la-juve-ha-preso-con-il-s-28236|title=Chi è Merih Demiral, il nuovo Vidic che la Juve ha preso con il Sassuolo|trans-title=Who is Demiral, the new Vidic that Juve acquired with Sassuolo|publisher=Calciomercato.com|last=Zanon|first=Federico|language=it|date=29 January 2019|access-date=14 January 2020|archive-date=14 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200114163520/https://www.calciomercato.com/news/chi-e-merih-demiral-il-nuovo-vidic-che-la-juve-ha-preso-con-il-s-28236|url-status=live}}</ref> Another one of his influences is his Juventus teammate [[Giorgio Chiellini]], to whom he has also been compared.<ref name=":0" /> He has also been likened to former Juventus defender [[Paolo Montero]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tuttojuve.com/lettera-del-tifoso/lettera-del-tifoso-massimiliano-demiral-nuovo-chiellini-non-si-puo-cedere-478519 |title=LETTERA DEL TIFOSO Massimiliano: "Demiral nuovo Chiellini, non si può cedere" |trans-title=Letter from a fan called Massimiliano: "Demiral new Chiellini, he can't be given away" |publisher=www.tuttojuve.com |language=it |date=22 July 2019 |access-date=17 January 2020 |archive-date=22 July 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190722152642/https://www.tuttojuve.com/lettera-del-tifoso/lettera-del-tifoso-massimiliano-demiral-nuovo-chiellini-non-si-puo-cedere-478519 |url-status=live }}</ref>

==Personal life==
Merih Demiral married the Albanian model Heidi Lushtaku in 2021.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=TheSportsGrail |last2=Shukla |first2=Rizu |date=2024-07-03 |title=Who is model Heidi Lushtaku wife of Merih Demiral, biography, age, children and Instagram |url=https://thesportsgrail.com/who-is-model-heidi-lushtaku-wife-of-merih-demiral-biography-age-children-and-instagram/ |access-date=2024-08-11 |website=The SportsGrail |language=en}}</ref>

On 20 April 2022, Demiral and his wife became the parents of a son and made this public a month after the birth.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://telegrafi.com/heidi-lushtaku-behet-nene-per-te-pare-zbulon-lidhjen-futbollistin-e-juventusit-merih-demiral/|title=Heidi Lushtaku bëhet nënë për herë të parë – zbulon lidhjen me futbollistin e njohur Merih Demiral|trans-title=Heidi Lushtaku becomes a mother for the first time – reveals the relationship with the famous footballer Merih Demiral|language=Albanian|publisher=[[Telegrafi]]|date=20 May 2022|access-date=20 May 2022|archive-date=20 May 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220520195221/https://telegrafi.com/heidi-lushtaku-behet-nene-per-te-pare-zbulon-lidhjen-futbollistin-e-juventusit-merih-demiral/|url-status=live}}</ref>

